Fix PotM South paragliding predictor — widen soarable direction window

The direction window was 140-220 deg (80 deg range) which was too
narrow. PotM South ridge faces SSW and is soarable in any wind with
a southerly component: 110-250 deg (140 deg range).

Key fixes:
- FPS ground truth is now the PRIMARY signal (was secondary to KPVU)
- KPVU demoted to secondary — it's 10mi south and often lags/misses
  the PotM thermal. Calm KPVU no longer kills the prediction.
- UTOLY confirmation window widened to 90-270 deg
- directionOK: 140-220 -> 110-250 (soarable range)
- directionIdeal: 135-210 (sweet spot for epic/excellent status)
- Speed range: 6-18 -> 5-20 mph (paragliders fly in wider range)
- Gust factor threshold: 1.35 -> 1.40 (PG pilots tolerate moderate)
- Peak hours widened: 8-14 -> 7-15
- Graduated scoring: ideal direction > good > marginal
- Config optimalDirection updated to match: 110-250 deg
